<p style="font-family:arial;font-size:15px;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;">
<img src="http://img.auctiva.com/imgdata/5/1/6/7/5/1/webimg/279764269_o.jpg" width="275" height="45" border="0">
<br /><br />
<p>&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: x-large;">Efficiency Decoration, Indian Volunteer Forces, George V issue, 1930-1935 with &lsquo;India&rsquo; clasp, miniature <br /></span></strong></p><p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: medium;">Miniature oval silver and silver-gilt skeletal badge in the form of an  oak wreath with loop for ribbon suspension, the silver-gilt crowned  cipher of King George V centrally; the reverse plain; height 23mm (0.9  inch); on original ribbon mounted for wear and with silver &lsquo;INDIA&rsquo;  clasp.  The Decoration was instituted on 17 October 1930 and replaced  the Territorial Decoration, being awarded to the same criteria, namely  20 years&rsquo; commissioned service, time in the ranks counting half and  service in wartime counting double.  This first version with the cipher  of King George V was replaced by that of King George VI in 1937.  A very  good period miniature.</span></p><p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align: left;"><link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CUsers%5Cnigel%5CAppData%5CLocal%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
