<p>&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: x-large;">Cross of Honour of the Parisian Society for the Encouragement of  Agriculture (Croix d''Honneur de la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; Parisienne d''Encouragement  Agricole) <br /></span></strong></p><p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: medium;">Seven-pointed ball-tipped white enamel and gilt star, a wreath of oak  and laurel between the arms, on gilt wreath of laurel and vines  suspension; the face with a gilt circular central stippled medallion  bearing a crowned escutcheon with fleurs de lys in chief, an  agricultural scene with two oxen ploughing below, all within a deep blue  enamel ring inscribed in gilt letters &lsquo;SOCIETE PARISIENNE  D&rsquo;ENCOURAGEMENT AGRICOLE&rsquo;; the reverse identical; on original ribbon  with the colours of Paris on a green ground.  The Society seems to have  disbanded many years ago leaving only a Medal and a Cross, both seen  occasionally,  marking its existence.  A good quality award.</span></p><p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align: left;"><link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CUsers%5Cnigel%5CAppData%5CLocal%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
